usage: git bundler [<options>] [--] [<bundle-path>...]

Register/list/configure bundle
- registration is done in in global zou-flow config file (~/.zou-flow)
- install git hooks

    -h|--help               display help
    -u|--unregister         unregister bundle path
    -s|--scan               scan and register bundles that are siblings of zou.
    -x|--external           configure external submodules
    -f|--force              force hooks update
    -q|--quiet              do not display submodules messages
    <bundle-path>...        bundle path
    
example:
    git bundler                     register and configure current bundle
    git bundler -s                  register and configure zou's sibling bundles
    git bundler -- bundle1 bundle2  register and configure bundle1 and bundle2
    git bundler -u                  unregister current bundle
